Stuck on the train with a vague AI answer? Here’s a quick fix.

Tell the AI what to do when it gets stuck. This is called error handling—like giving it a backup plan.

Try this:
Open your notes and find a prompt that didn’t work well. Add this to the end:
“If you can’t give a specific example, suggest three other ways to approach this.”

Run it again. You’ll get a better response.

Good prompting is about clear instructions. You just got better at it. (1/2)
